Date: 1-SEP-1995

Added #ifdef _AIX in pgpdaemon.c to wrap #include <sys/select.h>.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 25-SEP-1997

Grabbed new karma.h header and switched to use of ERRSTRING
macro. This should fix some portability problems, notably with FreeBSD
and BSDI.

Improved child process cleanup in pgpdaemon.c.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 27-SEP-1997

Created new file header.c and moved email address parsing code from
pgpsendmail.c

Changed header.c to add support for new address formats:
"Real Name"\n<username@email.address>
<username@email.address>

Created new programme extract-addrs which is a simple utility to extract
email addresses from a header.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 28-SEP-1997

Created new programme match-email-addr which is a simple utility to
match a list of email addresses with lists inside files. File lists
support simple address matching, regular expression matching and file
inclusion.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 29-SEP-1997

Modified pgpdaemon.c to support -uid <uid> command-line switch.
Modified pgpdaemon.c to encrypt (simply) in-memory copy of passphrase.
Modified pgpsendmail.h to fallback to SIGPOLL if SIGIO is not defined.
Included pgpsign code from Anthony Towns and modified.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 30-SEP-1997

Modified pgpdaemon.c to fix protocol: must always have trailing '\0'
character in ASCII messages.
Modified pgpdaemon.c to catch segmentation violations.
Modified pgpdaemon.c to support new "BINARY_DECRYPT" protocol.
